{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:22:17.279481+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:Lajxl7 | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 66328420ac4a69b088f99ae399388044682c17f2)", "id": "lc_2b9e097d-eba6-4c20-9e1e-5fea851f511c"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:Lajxl7 | # Book sources\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | \n| MCP:Lajxl7 | The app fetches public-domain books from the sources listed below. None of\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | them require a user-bound API key; the only authentication some endpoints\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | accept is a server-side rate-limit token shipped via CI secrets.\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | \n| MCP:Lajxl7 | | Source | Endpoint | Auth | Notes |\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | |--------|----------|------|-------|\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | | Feedbooks (public) | `https://catalog.feedbooks.com/catalog/public_domain.atom` | none | OPDS catalog |\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | | Project Gutenberg mirror | `https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/...` | none | HTML scraping |\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | | Internet Archive Bookreader | `https://archive.org/details/...` | none | OAuth optional for higher rate limits |\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | | Standard Ebooks | `https://standardebooks.org/feeds/atom/all` | none | Atom feed |\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | \n| MCP:Lajxl7 | If you add a new source, append a row above and update the test fixture in\n| MCP:Lajxl7 | `test/services/source_fixtures_test.dart`.", "id": "lc_0b7bd6cb-d191-4124-86a5-849465859327"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "896045f6-074e-48f6-925a-1a6ba0bb715c", "tool_call_id": "call_73b8ed977b78457ab95c1dfe", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
