{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:22:51.727819+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository's `docs/sources.md` (the authoritative source list), the app reads from the following external book sources:\n\n| Source | Endpoint | Authentication |\n|--------|----------|----------------|\n| **Feedbooks (public)** | `https://catalog.feedbooks.com/catalog/public_domain.atom` | **Anonymous** – no API key or token required. |\n| **Project Gutenberg mirror** | `https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/...` | **Anonymous** – no API key or token required. |\n| **Internet Archive Bookreader** | `https://archive.org/details/...` | **Anonymous** (basic access). *Optional OAuth* can be used for higher rate limits. |\n| **Standard Ebooks** | `https://standardebooks.org/feeds/atom/all` | **Anonymous** – no API key or token required. |\n\n**Notes from the documentation:**\n- The README mentions “Feedbooks token” and “Gutenberg mirror token,” but `docs/sources.md` clarifies that *none of the sources require a user‑bound API key*. Any tokens referenced are server‑side rate‑limit tokens used by the CI pipeline, not something end‑users must supply.\n- Internet Archive’s OAuth is explicitly labeled as optional and only needed for elevated rate limits.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 343, "prompt_tokens": 12191, "total_tokens": 12534, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 76, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 11200}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "a076688e362545d78b1dfb3cfed997cb", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead68-6561-73b0-b35f-4e41eee438aa-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12191, "output_tokens": 343, "total_tokens": 12534, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 11200}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 76}}}}]}}}
